data.description:
When I was 19 I was in a Call of Duty tournament online. And no, THAT is not what I am ashamed of. I was living in the middle of the desert in Southern California, I had a well on the property - the water for my house was not drinkable, it has a lot of heavy metals in it, it's barely good enough to shower with. I was sure to get a good night's sleep before the tourney began but I overslept and didn't realize I had no time to run into town - I'm also about 9 miles from the nearest store. 

I was scheduled in my tiers for Free-For-All, Hardcore Team Deathmatch, Kill Confirmed, and Capture the Flag. Unfortunately, since I was involved in so many of the brackets (pretty much all except TDM and Domination) I couldn't leave my house for pretty much the whole day. About 10 hours into the tournament, me and my team were in our bracket match for Capture the Flag. We had just played a match and my mouth was REALLY dry because I had nothing to drink. My voice started to get hoarse and I had trouble speaking about halfway through the match. 

After the match, I decide enough is enough - I've got about 20 minutes before my next match. I run out to my car fire it up.... car won't start. (Found out later that my starter had worn out) Out of desperation, I have an idea. 

"Where can I get a drink? Domino's has drinks!!!" 

Two issues with this. One, I've never ordered food at this address before and I live in the middle of nowhere, so I'm not sure they even come out this far. Two, I'm lactose-intolerant, despite loving pizza I really shouldn't eat it and their other items don't really interest me much... 

I call them up, give them my address. No dice, I'm outside of their delivery area, but the lady says I'm "just" outside the delivery area. Turns out, the delivery area is defined by my street. So I give him the address of my neighbor across the street. Bingo! The system takes it, she notes on the order that I'm across the street from this address. (I'm in love with this chick right now...) This dominos has a large coverage area, for my distance the minimum order is $35. 2-liters of Coke costs $2.99... 

"Fuck it..." 

I order $35 worth of overpriced 2-liters of Coke and Sprite. The lady can hardly believe it and asks me to repeat myself, I barely can with my dry throat and start to cough. Manager gets on the phone and I try to explain that this isn't a prank. He makes me pay over the phone with a credit card and charges me right then and there. He finalizes the order by saying: 

"Ok... well, I guess it's not against policy to send 10 2-liters and no food... They'll be there in about 45 minutes."

"45 minutes?!?! You don't need to cook soda, man!" *cough*

"Right... forgot about that... Maybe 15 minutes..." *hangs up*

Match starts, can't even talk - don't even bother putting my headset on, team's getting pissy. Match ends quick because I'm sucking horribly. Team is yelling what I can only assume are polite words of positive encouragement from my headset on the end table. I hear a horn outside, go to the door. FML, I didn't unlock the gate. Quickly take off as fast as my dehydrated ass can go down the driveway, about 1/8 mile long, get to the gate - forgot my fucking keys. 

Driver looking at me in terror as I hop the gate of my own property. Can barely stand, wobble over to the door. Tell him "Thirsty" he reached for one of the drinks in the back. Head pounding beyond belief. He hands me a coke, it's warm... and it's Diet Coke (which I didn't order)... "Fuck it..." said the stupid part of my brain. 

I crack it open and immediately put it to my mouth and begin to chug the bottle. Can't breathe after a few seconds, gasped mid gulp... inhaled a lungfull of hot CO2 gas... drop the bottle... fall backwards... black out for a few seconds. 

Dude is standing over me on his cell phone. Now I get to hear the story from his perspective. 

"This guy just came charging down his driveway at me, I think he's high or something. He started yelling and smacking the gate and then jumped over it. He ran to my car and yelled 'Burpee!' So I gave him a soda. He just started chugging it and collapsed, I think he's dying!" 

I tell him I'm ok and he gets off the phone. Turns out that wasn't the 911 or even his manager, it was his mother. This experience was so scary for him, he called his mother immediately...  Anyway, he puts the receipt in my face and hands me a pen.

"I need you to sign this." 

I sign it and fill in a $8 tip out of embarrassment. He helps me jump my own fence and hands me grocery bags with soda in it. I slowly make my way back to my house. Defeated - and drenched in warm Diet Coke - I strip my clothes off and go to the shower to rinse myself, now sipping on a cold Sprite... Yes, directly out of the 2-liter, I ain't classy. 

LESSONS LEARNED:
-Always keep emergency water supplies
-Don't be a loser with no IRL people who can save your dehydrating ass
-Get an electronic gate opener
-Even when you don't order pizza, Domino's will still get the order wrong
-Call of Duty is cancer
-Inhaling CO2 can make you temporarily black out

TL;DR: @OP severely dehydrated, orders $35 worth of soda from Domino's and traumatizes the delivery driver.

data.title: Screw imgur's ever changing fp standards. Here's Aunt Janet.
data.description:
Every. single. holiday. I would get a letter in the mail from Aunt Janet. In it would be a dollar store greeting card for whatever holiday it was, and a picture of her in it. Even though I'm grown, married, and literally live on the other corner of the country i still get about 15 cards and pictures of Aunt Janet. 

I use to hate it, and would only open the card for the slim chance of there being money in it (only for Christmas and birthdays) but as I've gotten older I've realized that the reason she does it is because she misses me, and doesn't want me to forget what my Aunt Janet looks like.

data.title: Shark demands petting every day
data.description:
Each day, Jordan and others he leads into that undersea realm are greeted by an 8-foot-long lemon shark whom he's named Blondie.

"She recognizes me as soon as I go in the water and runs over to me. It almost looks like she's smiling. She doesn't want food, she just wants to be petted," Jordan told The Dodo. "If you don't give her the attention, she'll bump into you. You have to attend to her. That's just the way she is. It is strange."
